PLEASANT HILL, Calif. (AP) — A San Francisco Bay Area man has been arrested after police found an incendiary device and bomb-making materials in his apartment, authorities said.The 27-year-old man, who has not been identified, came under police scrutiny after detectives police connected him to a string of vandalisms that happened in the Contra Costa County cities of Pleasant Hill and Clayton. Investigators obtained a search warrant for his home in Pleasant Hill after learning he had purchased bomb-making materials, the city’s police Sgt. Janayla Pierson said in a statement. The suspect was found at home along with explosive materials during Friday’s search, she said. Residents of about 20 units in the apartment building were ordered to shelter in place or evacuate during the search. Police said two bomb squads and a Hazmat unit responded to the scene to render his apartment safe.